Greece’s Olympus Invests $80 Million in Romanian Plant, ZF Says

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-07-01T06:40:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/greece-s-olympus-invests-80-million-in-romanian-plant-zf-says.html
Olympus Foods SA, a Greek privately
held company, invested 55 million euros ($80 million) in a new
factory in  Romania ,  Ziarul Financiar  reported today, citing the
company’s Chief Executive Officer Dimitrios Sarantis.  The factory, located near the city of Brasov in central
Romania, will produce  milk products  for export to the European
Union and the U.S., the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  